      "Employee returned to full unrestricted duty on August 5, 2014"
    ],
    "summary": "On July 18, 2014, at approximately 1140 hours, an employee of Baker Hughes sustained a fractured and partially amputated finger while assisting the crane operator in transferring chemicals from a tote tank to a storage tank on the Ensco 8502 drilling rig in Green Canyon 237. The tote tank was hoisted by crane and suspended outside the handrail for gravity-fed transfer. After connecting a camlock hose, the employee placed his left hand on the handrail to raise himself. Due to rough seas (6 ft. sea state), the suspended tank swayed and struck the employee's ring finger.",
